<TITLE> Malaysia opposition parties agree formal alliance </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kuala Lampur, April 1 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Malaysia's opposition parties have agreed to enter into a formal coalition, de facto opposition leader Anwar Ibrahim said on Tuesday, in an effort to present the parties as a credible alternative for government. The three main opposition parties won a record number of seats in parliament at elections on March 8, dealing the ruling National Front coalition the biggest setback in its 50-year reign.
